{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1392256f-f95a-4d92-b0ab-2e34a8cf3fe7","content":"**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Here's what the test showed:\n\n```\nSpan<nint>:  0, 10, 20, 30\nSpan<nuint>: 0, 20, 40, 60\nnint size: 8 bytes\n```\n\nBoth `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>` work with `stackalloc` just like any other unmanaged type. The only caveat is that `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context since the size is platform-dependent (8 bytes on this 64-bit machine, 4 on 32-bit).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"99e984d1-afc0-4a4b-a5b3-9f8cf7e42aca","outputTokens":175,"requestId":"B44A:69BE5:6EE759F:7A644B8:69F15627"},"id":"1c8d2b49-64ca-406b-b2ef-ea36a2ee5c29","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:51:56.587Z","parentId":"76f98802-6616-4a59-921d-4b5debea49d5"}
